<HEAD>Robber Killed At Highway Tollbooth</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CASERTA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who robbed several motorists at a
highway rest stop was killed by police in a shootout at a tollbooth.
   Police said the unidentified man held up several motorists at a
rest stop gas station and was later stopped by police at a
tollbooth near Naples.
   The man tried to escape by reversing out of the tollbooth, but
crashed into a truck. He jumped out of his car and fired two guns
at police but missed them.
   Police fired back, striking him in the chest. He died later at a
hospital.
