<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Greece-Prison,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Put Down Uprising At Greek Prison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PIRAEUS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Riot police used tear gas to put down a
seven-hour rampage by more than 100 inmates at the top-security
Korydallos prison.
   The 121 prisoners rioted after learning that prisoner George
Kaleri, 19, committed suicide after a fight Tuesday in the prison
canteen, officials said.
   Riot police forced the prisoners back to their cells on
Wednesday after they had burned mattresses and broken furniture on
the roof of their prison wing. The prison is located just outside
the port city of Piraeus.
   According to police sources who spoke on condition of anonymity,
the prisoners also demanded improved medical care and an end to
alleged beatings and random searches of their cells by prison
guards.
