<HEAD>Democratic Candidates To Debate in Rochester, NY</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The League of Women Voters says all four
Democratic presidential candidates have agreed to participate in a
debate in Rochester, N.Y. three days before the delegate-rich New
York State primary election.
   The one-hour debate, scheduled for 5 p.m. on Saturday, April 16,
will be broadcast live by Cable News Network and National Public
Radio from the Eastman Theatre on the campus of the University of
Rochester.
   Cable News Network anchor Bernard Shaw and former NBC anchor
Edwin Newman will moderate the debate.
</TEXT>
