<HEAD>Robertson Scheduled to Address Nevada Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RENO, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican presidential hopeful Pat Robertson
will speak here April 23 at the state GOP convention, where his
backers are expected to dominate delegates to the state meeting,
according to his Nevada coordinator.
   Robertson is scheduled to speak on the final day of the
three-day session and may hold a fundraiser in Reno the evening
before, coordinator Steve Wark said on Wednesday.
   Rep. Newt Gingrich, R-Ga., will give the keynote address to the
convention. Other speakers scheduled are GOP National Committee
Chairman Frank Fahrenkopf of Reno. Nevada's Sen. Chic Hecht, Rep.
Barbara Vucanovich and Attorney General Brian McKay are also
scheduled to speak.
