<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 3rd Ld-Writethru, a0428,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Up Against Yen; Japanese Stocks At All-Time High</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout to UPDATE with closing figures. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices reached an all-time high today in
Tokyo following the overnight advance on Wall Street, while the
dollar also edged up against the Japanese yen.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which gained 195.82 points Wednesday, gained
another 265.02 points, or 0.99 percent, closing the day at
26,767.19.
   The dollar closed at 125.70 yen, the day's high, up 0.67 yen
from its close Wednesday of 125.03 yen. It had opened the day at
125.60 yen and traded between 125.40-125.70 yen
   ``The overnight advance on Wall Street and the stronger dollar
boosted the stock average,'' said Tadaaki Uehara of Wako Securities.
   Taeko Kobayashi of the Bank of Tokyo said the foreign exchange
market, ``which started volatile in the morning following the
overnight surge on Wall Street, now seems stable without anything
particular directing participants.''
   In New York on Wednesday, the Dow Jones industrial average
closed at 2,061.67, up 64.16 points over Tuesday's close.
</TEXT>
