<HEAD>London Share Prices Open Higher On Bullish N.Y., Tokyo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices opened broadly stronger in London
today following bullish runs in New York and Tokyo.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index jumped 20.2
points, or 1.2 percent, to 1,765.2 at 9:45 a.m.
   Traders said the market was focused on the rallies in New York
and Tokyo.
   Rumors of an agreement among the Group of Seven industrial
nations on a floor for the dollar, which helped stir the New York
rally, have been discounted, traders said.
   But they said enough confidence remains in equities to drag cash
into the market from British institutions in any case.
   ``There's a better global feeling,'' one trader said. Another
said he saw early today ``a lot of money coming in from outside the
market,'' referring to the considerable cash holdings of
institutional investors.
