<2ND_LINE>PM-Cambodia-Soviet,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Khmer Rouge Claim Killing Five Soviets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Khmer Rouge guerrillas said they
ambushed and killed five Soviet advisers along a strategic highway
in Cambodia, according to a radio report made available today.
   The clandestine radio of the Khmer Rouge army said the
guerrillas ambushed a Vietnamese vehicle March 29 traveling between
the capital, Phnom Penh, and the seaport of Kompong Som.
   The broadcast said 10 people in the vehicle were killed and 12
were wounded. Among the dead, the broadcast said, were five Soviet
advisers.
   The Khmer Rouge periodically claim to kill Soviet personnel
advising the Vietnamese-backed government in Cambodia. Most of the
reports cannot be confirmed by independent sources.
   The guerrillas are among three major groups fighting the
Vietnamese, who invaded Cambodia in 1978. The Soviets have a
sizable mission in Cambodia, which includes advisers in both
military and non-military fields.
</TEXT>
