<HEAD>Andre Polak, Architect of Atomium Monument, Dead at 74</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Architect Andre Polak, who helped
design the Brussels Atomium momument for the 1958 World Fair, has
died of a heart attack. He was 74.
   Polak, who died Saturday, created the structure along with his
brother, Jean, and an associate.
   The structure resembles an iron molecule to symbolize the power
of science, the atomic age and Belgian industrial acumen of the
1950s.
   The nine huge spheres of the 335-foot-tall Atomium still
dominate the cityscape of suburban Laken.
</TEXT>
