<HEAD>Nine Crewmen Rescued From South Korean Freighter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine crewmen from a South Korean freighter
were rescued and nine others were listed as missing after the
vessel sank off western Taiwan, maritime officials said Thursday.
   The crew of the 2,000-ton Western Hope was rescued by a Japanese
vessel and a Panama-registered freighter Monday off the Taiwanese
fishing port of Yunlin, 120 miles southwest of Taipei, according to
officials of Royal Steamship Co.
   The vessel sank Sunday off Yunlin while on its way to the
northern Keelung port, officials said. It had sailed from the South
Korean port of Pusan with an unspecified cargo.
