<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convicted drug smuggler told Congress today
he flew weapons into Costa Rica for the Contra guerrillas battling
the government of Nicaragua and returned to the United States with
drugs.
   Gary Betzner said George Morales, the man for whom he was
working, ``told me he had made a deal with the CIA to supply them
(the Contras). He wanted me to fly guns and ammunition to the
Contras and bring some contraband back.''
   Twice in July 1984, Betzner told a Senate Foreign Relations
subcommittee, he flew planeloads of small arms, including M-1here pending
charges, the reports said.
