<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--DeathCoverup     04-07 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Death Coverup,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Tries To Cover Up Death With Balloons, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man hoped to make his death look like
murder by using balloons to try to float the 1{-pound gun away,
police reports said.
   The Feb. 12 death of real estate broker Lee DeGray Gibson, 52,
was ruled a suicide. His body was found on a rock jetty on the
Arkansas River with a gunshot wound to the left side of his chest.
Police records say a pair of balloons were tied to a string which
was tied to a .32-caliber pistol found in the water.
   Sgt. Eddie Alexander said the gun would have floated away except
the string got wrapped around Gibson's hand.
   He said there was no obvious reason to make the death look like
a murder. Two life insurance policies taken out in 1985 and 1986
did not have suicide clauses in them and two-year contestability
clauses had expired.
</TEXT>
