<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Hancock-Corea     04-07 0104</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Hancock-Corea,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hancock, Corea, To Tour for Homeless</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jazz musicians Herbie Hancock and Chick Corea
will conduct a 20-city concert tour this summer in an effort to
raise $150,000 for the homeless, it was announced Thursday.
   The tour's sponsor, Philip Morris Cos., said the money will be
distributed to homeless-aid organizations by the National Coalition
for the Homeless.
   The tour begins June 1 in Seattle and stops are scheduled in
Denver, Chicago, Cleveland and New York before ending in Tampa, Fla.
   Hancock will perform with The Headhunters, with Michael Brecker
on saxophone. Corea will perform with his Electric Band.
