<1ST_LINE>r a AM-RinkMeltdown     04-07 0251</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Rink Meltdown,0258</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ice Rink Melts, Cancels Disney Show</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A meltdown at the Tarrant County
Convention Center left Disney's World On Ice in puddles and
hundreds of tiny Mickey Mouse and Snow White fans out in the cold.
   After a Tuesday opening that attracted more than 6,000 fans,
convention center officials had to cancel two performances
Wednesday when a blown fuse allowed the 80- by 200-foot rink to
melt.
   Disney characters _ including Doc, Happy, Sleepy, Grumpy,
Sneezy, Dopey and Bashful _ got an unscheduled day off.
   ``It's unbelievable,'' said Melvin Morgan, executive director of
the convention center. ``This has never happened to us before _ or
to them.''
   Greg Ericson, regional marketing director for the show,
estimated ticket sale losses ``anywhere from $40,000 to $200,000. I
think there may be some kind of insurance covering this, but I'm
not positive.''
   Morgan said convention center workers first noticed the blown
fuse had jammed a pump that is part of the ice-making refrigeration
system late Tuesday. But they didn't think the problem was serious.
   By Wednesday morning, most of the rink had turned to slush.
   A mechanical firm fixed the pump and fuse Wednesday afternoon,
but it took seven hours to freeze the half-inch of ice required for
the show.
   Morgan and Ericson said tickets for the canceled shows would be
honored at any of the remaining performances in Fort Worth and
shows next week in Dallas, or they can be turned in for a refund.
</TEXT>
