<HEAD>National Urban Coalition Appoints Acting CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Educator Ramona Hoage Edelin was named acting
chief executive officer of the National Urban Coalition on Thursday.
   ``I am confident that ... she will provide the coalition with
strong, effective, creative leadership as the organization moves to
better serve its constituences in the 1990s and beyond,'' said
coalition president M. Carl Holman.
   Edelin, a senior staff member of the coalition for 11 years, is
a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Fisk University and holds a Ph.D. in
philosophy from Boston University.
   She is the co-developer and executive director of ``Say YES to a
Youngster's Future,'' the organization's education program to
prepare low-income, minority children and females for the high-tech
careers and lifestyles of the future.
   Since its founding in 1967, the coalition has specialized in
building corporate-government-community partnerships to upgrade the
education, health care, housing and economy of the nation's urban
areas.
