<HEAD>Stock Prices Open Firm, Dollar Little Changed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices opened strong Friday, rising above the
all-time high reached the previous session on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange's key market index.
   The U.S. dollar was little changed in early foreign exchange
activity.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, up 258.05
points on Thursday, rose an additional 34.77 points to 26,803.99 in
the first 15 minutes of trading.
   The Nikkei's close of 26,769.22 points on Thursday topped the
previous record of 26,646.43 on Oct. 14, which was just before the
worldwide stock market crash.
   In foreign exchange, the dollar opened at 125.52 yen, down
slightly from Thursday's close of 125.70 yen.
