<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
200,645 cars and trucks this week, up from last week's 185,688,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 241,796 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 127,012 cars this
week, compared with 119,815 a week ago and 162,429 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 73,633, compared
with last week's 65,873 and last year's 79,367.
   Canadian automakers were to build 27,095 cars this week,
compared with 21,619 last week and 12,086 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 20,845, compared
with 15,487 last week and 18,565 in the same week last year.
