<2ND_LINE>BC-Glaverbel-AFG Industries,0139</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Glaverbel Completes Offer For 20 Percent of AFG Industries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Glaverbel S.A, a Belgian glass maker,
said Thursday it successfully completed an offer for a 20-percent
stake in AFG Industries Inc., a U.S. glass maker.
   Glaverbel said in a statement it is acquiring the stake for $6
million. In addition, the company is buying all of the Irvine,
Calif.-based company's preferred stock for $150 million.
   Glaverbel said AFG Industries will now be controlled by a
holding company called Clarity in which Glaverbel will have a 20
percent stake. AFG Industries' management will hold 25 percent of
Clarity and institutional investors the remaining 55 percent.
   After five years, Glaverbel will have the right to acquire the
shareholding of the institutional investors, giving it control of
the U.S. glass maker.
