<HEAD>Surging High-Tech Firm Posts Record Quarterly Sales</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Intel Corp., the surging
semiconductor manufacturer, said Thursday its profit more than
tripled in its latest fiscal quarter.
   Intel said it earned $94 million, or 54 cents a share, in the
three months ended March 26, up from $26 million, or 14 cents a
share, in the year-earlier quarter. Revenue rose 61 percent to a
record $636 million from $395 million.
   ``We are experiencing strong demand for microprocessors,
microcontrollers, memories, peripheral components and personal
computer platforms,'' Andrew S. Grove, Intel's president, said in a
news release.
