<FILEID>AP-NR-04-07-88 2039EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-PiedmontRates     04-07 0270</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Piedmont Rates,0280</2ND_LINE>
<TEXT>
   WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) _ Piedmont Airlines announced price
reductions Thursday on nonrefundable fares for tickets purchased by
April 17, joining two other airlines which cut prices earlier this
week.
   None of the fares exceed $198 roundtrip, including those for
transcontinental travel, and they apply to Piedmont flights between
noon on Mondays and noon on Thursdays throughout the U.S. route
system.
   The fares are available for flights scheduled between April 18
and June 15.
   ``The timing of this sale is perfect for parents hoping to
attend their children's graduation ceremonies at distant colleges
and universities, for couples planning budget honeymoons to extend
their travel range to include a Florida resort, and for kids to get
an extra visit from their grandparents,'' said J. Daniel Brock,
Piedmont's senior vice president of marketing.
   Once tickets are purchased, plans cannot be changed. The fares
may not apply to some routes served by Piedmont regional and
commuter airline partners.
   The price reduction comes two days after Eastern Airlines and
Continental Airlines, the nation's sixth-largest and fifth-ranked
airlines, respectively, said they were cutting some fares in
anticipation of a slack period coming up for leisure travel.
   Although there are some minor differences, Eastern and
Continental introduced similar programs. The non-refundable tickets
must be purchased by April 14 (starting Tuesday for Eastern and
Wednesday for Continental), and used for travel from April 18
through June 15.
   Passengers must travel between noon Monday and noon Thursday.
Round-trip travel and a Saturday night stay are required.
   Those restrictions limit the program to eight travel days in
April, 18 days in May and nine in June.
</TEXT>
